{
  "stem": "9168.7",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So I thanked them for the great honor but declined, with a big pay increase from my Denver court.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Then in-- that was-- that was really 1968.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "In 1969, I was teaching.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "That was Milwaukee, '68, '69.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I was teaching a seminar in Boston.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And the-- the Secretary of the Senate, who was a very influential man, very important man in the Senate, learned that I was teaching up there, and he telephoned me and asked me if I wouldn't please, when I finished there, go down to Washington and take a look at them and the capital, since I've never been to Washington.",
      "word_count": 60
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So my younger son, Peter, was with me at that time, and we decided we would do that.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Went down to Washington and to the capital and saw a beautiful city, and saw a capital that I was just in awe of.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was so impressed.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And so then I told them that yes, I would.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I would.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But there was no opening at that time.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But there-- in the future, there would be at some point.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And it was a matter of training one from being a court reporter to becoming a parliamentary reporter with all the proper parliamentary procedure under the Senate rules.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I-- I went, eventually was called back there out of my Denver court for weeks and months at a time, just like it's going on in Washington, DC right now. 30- and 24-hour days-- I mean, 30-- 33 hours nonstop over days, and-- which they're doing.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then the first appointment came permanent in the House of Representatives in 1972.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So I-- I was-- the Senate reporters knew I would take the first permanent appointment wherever it happened.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
